# Financial & Business Operations Analysis Project

## Overview
This is a self-initiated professional project designed to simulate real-world financial and business operations analysis typically performed in banking and financial services environments.

The project demonstrates practical skills in financial reporting, KPI tracking, process analysis, and data-driven decision-making.

## Objectives
- Analyze financial and operational data to track costs, budgets, and KPIs
- Identify trends, variances, and efficiency improvement opportunities
- Create management-ready insights and documentation
- Apply business analysis methodologies used in analyst roles

## Scope
- Budget and expense tracking
- KPI identification and performance monitoring
- Financial variance and trend analysis
- Business process mapping and workflow documentation
- Executive-level reporting and summaries

## Tools & Technologies
- Microsoft Excel (Advanced)
- Power BI (Dashboard Design)
- Business Process Documentation
- Financial & KPI Analysis Techniques

## Deliverables
- Financial and operational analysis documentation
- KPI and performance insights
- Business process and workflow documentation
- Management summary with recommendations

## Outcome
This project demonstrates hands-on experience in financial operations analysis, business reporting, and process improvement aligned with Business Analyst and Financial Operations roles.
